I do not know how to do `Merge Request`, sorry. The best of I can, attached small patch. Works for described use case, works for nautilus core (I mean all integration tests did pass). Maybe one day there will be somebody capable to turn it into `Merge Request`:
```patch
--- a/nautilus/src/nautilus-file.c	2018-11-04 16:28:06.553184773 +1000
+++ b/nautilus/src/nautilus-file.c	2018-11-04 16:32:56.910466850 +1000
@@ -719,11 +719,15 @@
                              GFileInfo         *info)
 {
     NautilusFile *file;
+    const gchar *filename;

     g_return_val_if_fail (NAUTILUS_IS_DIRECTORY (directory), NULL);
     g_return_val_if_fail (info != NULL, NULL);

-    file = NAUTILUS_FILE (g_object_new (NAUTILUS_TYPE_VFS_FILE, NULL));
+    filename = g_file_info_get_name (info);
+    g_return_val_if_fail (filename != NULL && *filename, NULL);
+
+    file = nautilus_directory_new_file_from_filename (directory, filename, FALSE);
     nautilus_file_set_directory (file, directory);

     update_info_and_name (file, info);

```

